            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost">Ceionio Ru</supplied>fio <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">Albino <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>iro</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimo</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>praef</abbr><ex>ecto</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">urbi iteru</supplied>m <expan><abbr>iud</abbr><ex>ici</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">sacrarum</supplied> <expan><abbr>cogn</abbr><ex>itionum</ex></expan> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/><certainty match="preceding-sibling::node()" locus="value"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Y: Es handelt sich eher um Ceionius Rufius Albinus, praef. urbi 389/91 als um seinen Vater C. Ceionius Rufius Volusianus signo Lampadius, praef. urbi 365/6. Material: hellgrauer Marmor. Die Tafel kam 1918 ins Museo Nazionale Romano. Eingabe des Textes nach Lesung und Ergänzung von G. Alföldy am 8.3.1989.</p>
            </div>
